ped by at least two magnitudes from the peak. We discuss our\nresults in the light of recent observations of flares in otherwise quiescent\ngalaxies and note the dependence of these results on further parameters, such\nas the star/hole mass ratio and the stellar orbit.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 7 Oct 2008 20:07:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
